{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644856","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644856"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:09:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:09:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18066"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18066","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18066"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0,0,0.95,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10780"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74919"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10780"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18066"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60419"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5425"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25134"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25944"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26128"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74919","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74919"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 78-year-old woman presents to the emergency department with a wrist fracture after a fall at home. She appears unkempt with poor personal hygiene. Multiple bruises of varying ages are noted on her arms and torso. Her daughter, who is her primary caregiver, appears dismissive of these findings and interrupts frequently when the patient attempts to speak.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe treating clinician raises concerns of elder abuse.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a key characteristic of elder abuse?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Predominantly involves financial exploitation alone","Affects exclusively those with cognitive impairment","Requires physical violence to meet diagnostic criteria","Involves multiple forms of mistreatment including neglect","Occurs only in institutional care settings"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that elder abuse \u003Cstrong\u003Einvolves multiple forms of mistreatment including neglect\u003C/strong\u003E. Elder abuse encompasses physical abuse, psychological or emotional abuse, financial exploitation, sexual abuse, and neglect. This comprehensive definition recognises that abuse can manifest in various ways, often with multiple forms occurring simultaneously.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPredominantly involves financial exploitation alone\u003C/strong\u003E - Although financial abuse is common, elder abuse encompasses various forms of mistreatment that frequently occur together.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAffects exclusively those with cognitive impairment\u003C/strong\u003E - While cognitive impairment increases vulnerability, elder abuse can affect any older person regardless of their cognitive function.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequires physical violence to meet diagnostic criteria\u003C/strong\u003E - Physical violence is not required for elder abuse, as psychological abuse, neglect, or financial exploitation alone constitute abuse.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOccurs only in institutional care settings\u003C/strong\u003E - Elder abuse occurs in any setting where older people live, including private homes, community settings, and aged care facilities.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, there are multiple concerning features suggesting abuse: poor hygiene indicating possible neglect, unexplained bruising suggesting physical abuse, and controlling behaviour by the caregiver suggesting psychological abuse.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Elder abuse includes physical, psychological, financial, and sexual abuse, as well as neglect of an older person.","Risk factors for elder abuse include social isolation, cognitive impairment, and dependency on caregivers.","Healthcare professionals have a legal and ethical obligation to report suspected cases of elder abuse."],"references":["Cimino-Fiallos N, Rosen T. Elder Abuse-A Guide to Diagnosis and Management in the Emergency Department. Emerg Med Clin North Am. 2021;39(2):405-417. doi:10.1016/j.emc.2021.01.009"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60419"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18066"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60419","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60419"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T12:14:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T12:16:27+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10780"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74919"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type"